name: r-tidyconsultant
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-tidyconsultant
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/TidyConsultant_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/TidyConsultant/TidyConsultant_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 42c7f85a77d3c81ce094bf7c405b6aa0a0ace56dea497c98306ad50eba05fbc6

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-autostats
    - r-badger
    - r-framecleaner
    - r-pacman
    - r-presenter
    - r-tidybins
    - r-validata
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-autostats
    - r-badger
    - r-framecleaner
    - r-pacman
    - r-presenter
    - r-tidybins
    - r-validata

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('TidyConsultant')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('TidyConsultant')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://harrison4192.github.io/TidyConsultant/, https://github.com/Harrison4192/TidyConsultant
  license: MIT
  summary: Loads the 5 packages in the Tidy Consultant Universe. This collection of packages
    is useful for anyone doing data science, data analysis, or quantitative consulting.
    The functions in these packages range from data cleaning, data validation, data
    binning, statistical modeling, and file exporting.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
